direct_enhancements.reason: Both methods generate ID numbers but with different validity outcomes (valid vs. invalid).
Both methods involve generating parts of the ID number with similar control flows and data handling.
The checksum method is used in both generateValid and generateInvalid to ensure or invalidate the ID number.
The firstDigit method is used in basePart, which is a dependency for generateValid.
The checksum method with coefficients is used in the main checksum method, which is a dependency for generateValid.
